r and employers more accountable. This is a book for anyone interested in issues of worker health and safety, and it will also serve as the cornerstone for courses in public policy, community health, labor studies, business ethics, regulation and safety, and occupational and environmental health policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHazardous occupationszUnited States. 0aIndustrial accidentszUnited States. 0aIndustrial hygienezUnited States. 0aIndustrial safetyzUnited States. 0aOccupational mortalityzUnited States. 4aLabor History. 4aLegal History & Studies. 4aSocial Work.  aoccupational safety, workplace injuries, labor rights, public policy, business ethics, health policy, employment law.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501714382?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714382423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714382/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles